context: <a0_0><b3_0><b4_0>A narthex<b4_0/><b3_0/><a0_0/> (a portico or entrance hall) for the west front was designed by Sir Edwin Lutyens in the <a1_0><b5_0>mid-20th century<b5_0/><a1_0/> but was not built. Images of the abbey prior to the construction of the towers are scarce, though the abbey's official website states that the building was without towers following <a2_0><b6_0><b7_0>Yevele<b7_0/><b6_0/><a2_0/>'s renovation, with just the lower segments beneath the roof level of the Nave completed.
